content:
Here is the cleaned-up text:

Salesforce generates a unique Embedded Service code snippet from the information you provide during setup. Copy and paste the code snippet to include chat on your web pages.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Embedded Service setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Embedded Chat: Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

Here are the steps to add your code snippet:

1. From Setup, enter Embedded Service in the Quick Find box.
2. Select Embedded Service and then select the deployment you want to work with.
3. Go to the Embedded Service configuration page and click Get Code.
4. Copy the chat code snippet and paste it above the closing </body> tag on your web page.
5. Optionally, customize the chat code snippet and add a meta tag for responsiveness.

Note: If there are issues with behavior on other devices, update your <meta> tag to the provided code snippet.

TIP If you're adding your Chat window to a Visualforce page, include these attributes on your apex:page tag.

Customize the Embedded Service Code Snippet
Use a text or HTML editor to customize the optional parameters in the Embedded Service code snippet.
Add Your Website to the CORS Allowlist
Add the URLs of the web pages where you intend to add the chat window to the CORS allowlist in your org.
title: Adding Embedded Service Chat to a Website
